result.execSummary:
The defendant Paul M Dupey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Repeater], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Paul M Dupey in court with Attorney M. Elizabeth Weathers.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Grant Scaife appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #4.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #4.  Counts #1-3 are dismissed and read-in.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Weathers makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #4:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

90 DAYS HUBER    *consecutive to any other sentence*

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR    *concurrent with any other sentence* 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs/drug paraphernalia 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are 
prescribed/sing releases.
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____No contact with: Brenda R.  or Jack S. or with Phoenix Bar in Hartland
____Mental Heath / Psychological Evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate

COSTS:  $243.00 & $200.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid out of cash bail posted ($100.00) and remainder due as a condition of probation)

*Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.*
